\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 Full Site Editing\cb1 \
\cb3 Apr 19, 2025\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Global Styles
\f1\b0  helps users change the style of their site without having to edit individual blocks or pages. It also lowers the entry barrier and makes it easier for theme developers to style blocks.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Theme.json 
\f1\b0 is a new theme configuration for block settings, site-wide styles, and block styles.\cb1 \
\cb3 In this lesson, you will learn what Global Styles are, how to create a theme.json file, and how you can benefit from Global Styles.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 What are Global Styles?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \'93Global Styles\'94 is both a system for loading CSS and an interface created to help users change the style of their site without having to edit individual blocks or pages. \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 From a theme developer perspective, Global Styles makes it easier to style blocks in the editor and front.\cb1 \
\cb3 Both classic PHP-based themes and block themes can take advantage of global styles using theme.json. 
\f2\b But only block themes use the new Styles interface.
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 The Styles interface\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 WordPress introduced the Styles interface as part of the Site Editor in version 5.9. You find the controls inside a separate sidebar panel in the Site Editor.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 First, access the Site Editor via Appearance > Editor in the WordPress admin.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Next, select the Styles menu item in the sidebar:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 In the Site Editor, you can open the Styles sidebar by clicking on the icon with the black and white split circle (next to the save button).\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 In the first panel, you can access options for typography, colors, and layout for the website:\cb1 \
