\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Template parts\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 With full site editing, there are three optional template part areas: header, footer, and uncategorized (general). You can assign a template part that you have designed as a header to the header 
\f3\i area
\f1\i0 . This helps users select the correct template parts when they are creating or editing their website.\cb1 \
\cb3 This section is at the base level of theme.json. The section name is 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 templateParts
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , followed by the template part slug (name) and the area. The title is the visible name in the editor.\cb1 \
\cb3 In the example, the template part file name is 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 header.htm
\f1\fs32 \cb3 l, which means that 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 header
\f1\fs32 \cb3  is the slug you need to use as a value for the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 name
\f1\fs32 \cb3  property:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb6 wp_template_part_area
\f1\fs32 \cb3  is a taxonomy for the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 wp_template_part
\f1\fs32 \cb3  post type.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Custom templates\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 With a traditional PHP-based theme, you place the required information in the file header of the template file:\cb1 \
\cb3 With full site editing, you can list templates in theme.json.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The section name is 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 customTemplates
\f1\fs32 \cb3  and just like the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 settings
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 styles
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , and 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 templateParts
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , the section is at the base level of theme.json.\cb1 \
\cb3 The first key is the name and slug of the template. In the example, I have named the template file 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 page-about.html
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , and the slug is 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 page-about
\f1\fs32 \cb3 .\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Patterns\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 The 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 patterns
\f1\fs32 \cb3  section was added to theme.json in Gutenberg version 12.7 to make it easier to include patterns from the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wordpress.org/patterns/"}}{\fldrslt \ul WordPress.org pattern directory.}}\cb1 \
\cb3 It is in the root level of theme.json and uses an array of block pattern slugs:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf7 \cb8 "patterns": [ "short-text-surrounded-by-round-images", "partner-logos" ]
